{"title_page": "Titans of Creation", "text_new": "{{Infobox album\n| name         = Titans of Creation\n| type         = studio\n| artist       = [[Testament (band)|Testament]]\n| cover        = Testament - Titans of Creation.jpg\n| alt          = \n| released     = April 3, 2020\n| recorded     = 2019\n| studio       = Trident Studios, Pacheco, CA, [[USA]]\n| length       = 58:34\n| label        = [[Nuclear Blast]]\n| genre        = [[Thrash metal]]\n| producer     =\n* [[Chuck Billy (vocalist)|Chuck Billy]]\n* [[Eric Peterson (musician)|Eric Peterson]]\n* Juan Urteaga\n| prev_title   = [[Brotherhood of the Snake]]\n| prev_year    = 2016\n| next_title   = \n| next_year    = \n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = Titans of Creation\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = Night of the Witch\n | single1date = January 31, 2020<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.blabbermouth.net/news/listen-to-new-testament-song-night-of-the-witch/|title=Listen To New TESTAMENT Song 'Night Of The Witch'|website=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|date=January 31, 2020|accessdate=January 31, 2020}}</ref>\n | single2     = Children of the Next Level\n | single2date = March 6, 2020<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.blabbermouth.net/news/listen-to-new-testament-song-children-of-the-next-level/|title=Listen To New TESTAMENT Song 'Children Of The Next Level'|website=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|date=March 6, 2020|accessdate=March 6, 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''Titans of Creation''''' is the thirteenth studio album by American [[thrash metal]] band [[Testament (band)|Testament]], released on April 3, 2020.<ref name=\"blabbermouth\">{{cite web|url=https://blabbermouth.net/news/testament-to-release-titans-of-creation-album-in-april-cover-artwork-track-listing-revealed/|title=TESTAMENT To Release 'Titans Of Creation' Album In April; Cover Artwork, Track Listing Revealed|website=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|date=January 30, 2020|accessdate=January 30, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"itunes\">{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/nz/album/titans-of-creation/1493544060|title=Titans of Creation by Testament|website=Apple Music|accessdate=January 30, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://loudwire.com/chuck-billy-testament-new-album-hopefully-april-2019/|title=Testament Detail 12th Album 'Titans of Creation'|website=[[Loudwire|Loudwire.com]]|date=January 30, 2020|accessdate=January 30, 2020}}</ref> This album marks the first time that Testament had recorded more than one album with the same lineup since ''[[The Ritual (Testament album)|The Ritual]]'' (1992). ''Titans of Creation'' is also the band's first album to be co-produced by Juan Urteaga, who previously worked with Testament's two studio albums ''[[Dark Roots of Earth]]'' (2012) and ''[[Brotherhood of the Snake]]'' (2016).\n\n==Background, writing and recording==\nTestament's intention to follow-up ''Brotherhood of the Snake'' was first revealed by [[Chuck Billy (vocalist)|Chuck Billy]] in March 2017, who told Japan's Roppongi Rocks that the band had begun writing new material.<ref>{{cite web|title=Testament Is Already Working On Material For Next Album|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/testament-is-already-working-on-material-for-next-album/|work=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|date=March 13, 2017|accessdate=January 30, 2020}}</ref> Billy also expressed hope that the album would be released in 2018, stating, \"We thought we'd have a record out after two years; it just ended up being four, because the process just... I don't know what happened, but it took forever. So this time, like, you know what? I don't wanna do that again. I told Eric exactly when we were done recording. I said, 'You know what? It's a great record now, but I don't wanna go through what I had to go through to do this again. So why don't we start writing now?' So we decided that when we're not on the road, let's get together and just jam and maybe come up and at least get to that point where we were with this record \u2014 a bunch of ideas and riffs and lyrics.\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Testament Hopes To Release Next Album In 2018|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/testament-hopes-to-release-next-album-in-2018/|work=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|date=March 20, 2017|accessdate=January 30, 2020}}</ref> In a December 2017 interview with Metal Messiah Radio, Billy stated that Testament would start working on their thirteenth studio album after they finish touring in support of ''Brotherhood of the Snake'' in August 2018, hoping not to repeat the four year gaps between their last three albums. He explained, \"If we can get a head start on riffs and ideas, and then hopefully after that, you know, really dig in to put out a record in 2019, sometime.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ultimate-guitar.com/news/community_feed/testament_no_new_album_until_next_year.html|title=Testament: No New Album Until Next Year|website=Ultimate-Guitar.com|date=March 19, 2018|accessdate=January 30, 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn a February 2018 interview with RockSverige, guitarist [[Eric Peterson (musician)|Eric Peterson]] said, \"Our plan was to end in August 2018 and maybe get into the studio by the end of 2018 and put the record out in 2019. But, you know, [[Slayer]]'s announced their [[Slayer Farewell Tour|farewell tour]] and they want us to be a part of it. I would imagine, if that stuff happens, then things will get pushed back a little bit, but the initial plan is to have it out in 2019. [We're] ready for summer to do all the A markets for festivals and stuff. This summer we're not doing a lot of festivals; we're actually talking about bowing out of a couple to make other things happen with the Slayer farewell thing.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/testament-hopes-to-release-new-studio-album-in-2019/|title=TESTAMENT Hopes To Release New Studio Album In 2019|website=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|date=April 2, 2018|accessdate=January 30, 2020}}</ref> Billy stated in a May 2018 interview that opening for Slayer on their farewell tour would be \"the final lap for [them] touring\" in support of ''Brotherhood of the Snake'', and added, \"We want our focus, during this and after this, to dive back into the songwriting process. We want to release a new album in 2019, so we need to get started soon.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/testaments-chuck-billy-we-want-to-release-a-new-album-in-2019/|title=TESTAMENT's CHUCK BILLY: 'We Want To Release A New Album In 2019'|website=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|date=May 9, 2018|accessdate=January 30, 2020}}</ref> A month later, Billy told [[Full Metal Jackie]] that, \"the goal is to get in the studio hopefully by January and have a record out hopefully by April.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/testament-frontman-hopes-to-begin-recording-new-album-in-january/|title=TESTAMENT Frontman Hopes To Begin Recording New Album In January|website=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|date=July 24, 2018|accessdate=January 30, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://loudwire.com/chuck-billy-testament-new-album-hopefully-april-2019/|title=Chuck Billy: Testament's New Album 'Hopefully' Out April of 2019|website=[[Loudwire|Loudwire.com]]|date=June 25, 2018|accessdate=January 30, 2020}}</ref> He also told ''Metal Heads Forever Magazine'' that, \"Me and Eric, we'll start really just creating and working, trying to get the next record out as soon as possible, because we have plans and hopes of setting a deadline on ourselves to have it out by summer 2019. We've got a lot of work ahead of us.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/testaments-chuck-billy-the-goal-is-to-have-next-album-out-by-summer-2019/|title=TESTAMENT's CHUCK BILLY: The Goal Is To Have Next Album Out 'By Summer 2019'|website=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|date=July 31, 2018|accessdate=January 30, 2020}}</ref> Billy told ''Talking Metal'' podcast in August 2018 that the band would start work on the new album after their tour with Slayer, and added, \"Our hopes and dreams would be to get in the studio by January and have an album out by the summer.\" He also said that they would work with [[Andy Sneap]] as the album's mixer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/testament-frontman-its-time-to-buckle-down-and-try-to-get-some-music-written/|title=TESTAMENT Frontman: 'It's Time To Buckle Down And Try To Get Some Music Written'|website=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|date=August 8, 2018|accessdate=January 30, 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn a January 2019 interview with Jimmy Kay of Canada's The Metal Voice, Billy confirmed that Testament had been writing songs for their thirteenth album, and added, \"We should have it out hopefully by July. Hopefully we'll get into the studio by April. That's the goal.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/testaments-chuck-billy-on-next-album-hopefully-well-get-into-the-studio-by-april/|title=TESTAMENT's CHUCK BILLY On Next Album: 'Hopefully We'll Get Into The Studio By April'|website=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|date=January 26, 2019|accessdate=January 30, 2020}}</ref> A month later, Billy announced on social media that work on the new album had started,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://metaladdicts.com/site/testament-are-working-on-new-album/|title=TESTAMENT Are Working On New Album|website=MetalAddicts.com|date=February 8, 2019|accessdate=January 30, 2020}}</ref> and pre-production began in May.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/testament-in-pre-production-for-new-album-its-gonna-be-a-monster-record/|title=TESTAMENT In Pre-Production For New Album: 'It's Gonna Be A Monster Record'|website=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|date=May 5, 2019|accessdate=January 30, 2020}}</ref> Drummer [[Gene Hoglan]] revealed in a June 2019 interview on the \"Talk Toomey\" podcast that the band had finished recording the album for a 2019 or early 2020 release.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/testament-has-finished-recording-new-album-says-gene-hoglan/|title=TESTAMENT Has Finished Recording New Album, Says GENE HOGLAN|website=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|date=June 18, 2019|accessdate=January 30, 2020}}</ref> Peterson announced later that month that it would be released in January 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/testaments-new-album-to-be-released-in-january-2020/|title=TESTAMENT's New Album To Be Released In January 2020|website=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|accessdate=June 23, 2019|date=June 23, 2019}}</ref> In an interview at a [[Metal Allegiance]] concert in Anaheim on January 16, 2020, Billy revealed that the then-still-untitled album would be released on April 3.<ref name=\"april2020\">{{cite web|url=https://www.blabbermouth.net/news/testaments-new-album-gets-official-release-date/|title=TESTAMENT's New Album Gets Official Release Date|website=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|accessdate=January 18, 2020|date=January 18, 2020}}</ref> It was later revealed that the album would be titled ''Titans of Creation''.<ref name=\"blabbermouth\" /><ref name=\"itunes\"/>\n\n==Reception==\n{{Album ratings\n<!-- Aggregate scores -->\n| MC         = \n<!-- Reviewers -->\n| rev1       = [[Blabbermouth.net]]\n| rev1Score  = 8/10<ref name=\"blabbermouth.net\">{{cite web |url=https://www.blabbermouth.net/cdreviews/titans-of-creation/|title=CD Reviews - Titans Of Creation Testament|last=Roche|first=Jason|publisher=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|accessdate=April 10, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev2       = [[KNAC]]\n| rev2Score  = 3.5/5<ref name=\"knac.com\">{{cite web |url=http://knac.com/article.asp?ArticleID=35913|title=KNAC.COM - Reviews - TESTAMENT 'Titans Of Creation'|last=Atkinson|first=Peter|publisher=[[KNAC|knac.com]]|date=April 3, 2020|accessdate=April 10, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev3       = [[Metal Storm (webzine)|Metal Storm]]\n| rev3Score  = 6.0/10<ref name=\"Metal Storm\">{{cite web |title= Testament - Titans Of Creation review |url=http://metalstorm.net/pub/review.php?review_id=15485 |publisher=Metal Storm |accessdate=12 April 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n''Titans of Creation'' has received positive reviews from critics. Jason Roche of [[Blabbermouth.net]] gave the album a rating of eight out of ten and said, \"While Testament has in the past shown to be capable of much more in terms of lyrics and songcraft, the fact that the band is using their power in 2020 to simply put out a killer thrash record full of songs about well-worn topics such as World War III, serial killers from a generation ago, and the [[Heaven's Gate (religious group)|Heaven's Gate]] suicide cult is comforting and very welcome.\"<ref name=\"blabbermouth.net\" /> [[KNAC|KNAC.com]] contributor Peter Atkinson, who rated ''Titans of Creation'' 3.5 out of five, called it \"sort of kick in the ass we could all use right now. And the album most definitely kicks ass.\"<ref name=\"knac.com\" />\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n| title1 = Children of the Next Level\n| lyrics1 = {{hlist|[[Chuck Billy (vocalist)|Chuck Billy]]|[[Del James]]}}\n| music1 = [[Eric Peterson]]\n| length1 = 6:13\n| title2 = WWIII\n| lyrics2 = {{hlist|Billy|James}}\n| music2 = Peterson\n| length2 = 4:48\n| title3 = Dream Deceiver\n| lyrics3 = {{hlist|Billy|James}}\n| music3 = Peterson\n| length3 = 4:58\n| title4 = Night of the Witch\n| lyrics4 = {{hlist|Billy|Peterson|James}}\n| music4 = Peterson\n| length4 = 6:32\n| title5 = City of Angels\n| lyrics5 = {{hlist|Billy|James}}\n| music5 = Peterson\n| length5 = 6:43\n| title6 = Ishtar's Gate\n| lyrics6 = {{hlist|Billy|James}}\n| music6 = Peterson\n| length6 = 5:09\n| title7 = Symptoms\n| lyrics7 = [[Alex Skolnick]]\n| music7 = Skolnick\n| length7 = 4:37\n| title8 = False Prophet\n| lyrics8 = {{hlist|Billy|[[Steve Souza|Steve \"Zetro\" Souza]]}}\n| music8 = Peterson\n| length8 = 4:54\n| title9 = The Healers\n| lyrics9 = {{hlist|Billy|James}}\n| music9 = Peterson\n| length9 = 4:23\n| title10 = Code of Hammurabi\n| lyrics10 = {{hlist|Billy|Skolnick|James}}\n| music10 = Skolnick\n| length10 = 4:52\n| title11 = Curse of Osiris\n| lyrics11 = {{hlist|Billy|James}}\n| music11 = Peterson\n| length11 = 3:24\n| title12 = Catacombs\n| lyrics12 = ''Instrumental''\n| music12 = Peterson\n| length12 = 2:01\n| total_length = 58:34\n}}\n\n{{Track listing\n| headline = Japanese special edition bonus CD - Recorded live at [[Shibuya O-East|Tsutaya O-East]] in [[Shibuya]], [[Tokyo]], Japan on February 20th, 2017.\n| title1 = Brotherhood of the Snake\n| length1 = \n| title2 = Rise Up\n| length2 = \n| title3 = Disciples of the Watch\n| length3 =\n| title4 = The Pale King\n| length4 = \n| title5 = Practice What You Preach\n| length5 = \n| title6 = The New Order\n| length6 = \n| title7 = More Than Meets the Eye\n| length7 = \n| title8 = Dark Roots of Earth\n| length8 = \n| title9 = Stronghold\n| length9 = \n| title10 = Into the Pit\n| length10 =\n| title11 = Over the Wall\n| length11 =\n| title12 = D.N.R. (Do Not Resuscitate)\n| length12 =\n| title13 = 3 Days in Darkness\n| length13 =\n| title14 = The Formation of Damnation\n| length14 =\n| title15 = Alone in the Dark\n| length15 =\n}}\n\n==Personnel==\n* [[Chuck Billy (vocalist)|Chuck Billy]] \u2013 lead vocals, producing\n* [[Eric Peterson (musician)|Eric Peterson]] \u2013 rhythm and lead guitar, vocals, producing\n* [[Alex Skolnick]] \u2013 lead guitar\n* [[Steve Di Giorgio]] \u2013 bass\n* [[Gene Hoglan]] \u2013 drums\n\n===Additional personnel===\n* Lyle Livingston \u2013 keyboards on track 12\n* Greg Ross \u2013 vocals\n* Rigo Martin \u2013 vocals\n* Juan Urteaga \u2013 co-producing, recording\n* [[Andy Sneap]] \u2013 mixing, mastering\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2020)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Australian Albums ([[ARIA Charts|ARIA]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ariacharts.com.au/charts/albums-chart|title=ARIA Australian Top 50 Albums|publisher=[[Australian Recording Industry Association]]|date=April 13, 2020|accessdate=April 11, 2020}}</ref>\n| 30\n|-\n{{album chart|Flanders|175|artist=Testament|album=Titans of Creation|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 10, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Wallonia|147|artist=Testament|album=Titans of Creation|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 10, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Finland|6|artist=Testament|album=Titans of Creation|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 12, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Germany4|3|id=405347|artist=Testament|album=Titans of Creation|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 10, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Oricon|29|date=2020-04-13|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 8, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Scotland|52|date=20200410|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 11, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|UKRock|4|date=20200410|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 11, 2020}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Testament}}\n\n[[Category:2020 albums]]\n[[Category:Testament (band) albums]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox album\n| name         = Titans of Creation\n| type         = studio\n| artist       = [[Testament (band)|Testament]]\n| cover        = Testament - Titans of Creation.jpg\n| alt          = \n| released     = April 3, 2020\n| recorded     = 2019\n| studio       = Trident Studios, Pacheco, CA, [[USA]]\n| length       = 58:34\n| label        = [[Nuclear Blast]]\n| genre        = [[Thrash metal]]\n| producer     =\n* [[Chuck Billy (vocalist)|Chuck Billy]]\n* [[Eric Peterson (musician)|Eric Peterson]]\n* Juan Urteaga\n| prev_title   = [[Brotherhood of the Snake]]\n| prev_year    = 2016\n| next_title   = \n| next_year    = \n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = Titans of Creation\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = Night of the Witch\n | single1date = January 31, 2020<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.blabbermouth.net/news/listen-to-new-testament-song-night-of-the-witch/|title=Listen To New TESTAMENT Song 'Night Of The Witch'|website=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|date=January 31, 2020|accessdate=January 31, 2020}}</ref>\n | single2     = Children of the Next Level\n | single2date = March 6, 2020<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.blabbermouth.net/news/listen-to-new-testament-song-children-of-the-next-level/|title=Listen To New TESTAMENT Song 'Children Of The Next Level'|website=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|date=March 6, 2020|accessdate=March 6, 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''Titans of Creation''''' is the thirteenth studio album by American [[thrash metal]] band [[Testament (band)|Testament]], released on April 3, 2020.<ref name=\"blabbermouth\">{{cite web|url=https://blabbermouth.net/news/testament-to-release-titans-of-creation-album-in-april-cover-artwork-track-listing-revealed/|title=TESTAMENT To Release 'Titans Of Creation' Album In April; Cover Artwork, Track Listing Revealed|website=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|date=January 30, 2020|accessdate=January 30, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"itunes\">{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/nz/album/titans-of-creation/1493544060|title=Titans of Creation by Testament|website=Apple Music|accessdate=January 30, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://loudwire.com/chuck-billy-testament-new-album-hopefully-april-2019/|title=Testament Detail 12th Album 'Titans of Creation'|website=[[Loudwire|Loudwire.com]]|date=January 30, 2020|accessdate=January 30, 2020}}</ref> This album marks the first time that Testament had recorded more than one album with the same lineup since ''[[The Ritual (Testament album)|The Ritual]]'' (1992). ''Titans of Creation'' is also the band's first album to be co-produced by Juan Urteaga, who previously worked with Testament's two studio albums ''[[Dark Roots of Earth]]'' (2012) and ''[[Brotherhood of the Snake]]'' (2016).\n\n==Background, writing and recording==\nTestament's intention to follow-up ''Brotherhood of the Snake'' was first revealed by [[Chuck Billy (vocalist)|Chuck Billy]] in March 2017, who told Japan's Roppongi Rocks that the band had begun writing new material.<ref>{{cite web|title=Testament Is Already Working On Material For Next Album|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/testament-is-already-working-on-material-for-next-album/|work=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|date=March 13, 2017|accessdate=January 30, 2020}}</ref> Billy also expressed hope that the album would be released in 2018, stating, \"We thought we'd have a record out after two years; it just ended up being four, because the process just... I don't know what happened, but it took forever. So this time, like, you know what? I don't wanna do that again. I told Eric exactly when we were done recording. I said, 'You know what? It's a great record now, but I don't wanna go through what I had to go through to do this again. So why don't we start writing now?' So we decided that when we're not on the road, let's get together and just jam and maybe come up and at least get to that point where we were with this record \u2014 a bunch of ideas and riffs and lyrics.\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Testament Hopes To Release Next Album In 2018|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/testament-hopes-to-release-next-album-in-2018/|work=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|date=March 20, 2017|accessdate=January 30, 2020}}</ref> In a December 2017 interview with Metal Messiah Radio, Billy stated that Testament would start working on their thirteenth studio album after they finish touring in support of ''Brotherhood of the Snake'' in August 2018, hoping not to repeat the four year gaps between their last three albums. He explained, \"If we can get a head start on riffs and ideas, and then hopefully after that, you know, really dig in to put out a record in 2019, sometime.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ultimate-guitar.com/news/community_feed/testament_no_new_album_until_next_year.html|title=Testament: No New Album Until Next Year|website=Ultimate-Guitar.com|date=March 19, 2018|accessdate=January 30, 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn a February 2018 interview with RockSverige, guitarist [[Eric Peterson (musician)|Eric Peterson]] said, \"Our plan was to end in August 2018 and maybe get into the studio by the end of 2018 and put the record out in 2019. But, you know, [[Slayer]]'s announced their [[Slayer Farewell Tour|farewell tour]] and they want us to be a part of it. I would imagine, if that stuff happens, then things will get pushed back a little bit, but the initial plan is to have it out in 2019. [We're] ready for summer to do all the A markets for festivals and stuff. This summer we're not doing a lot of festivals; we're actually talking about bowing out of a couple to make other things happen with the Slayer farewell thing.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/testament-hopes-to-release-new-studio-album-in-2019/|title=TESTAMENT Hopes To Release New Studio Album In 2019|website=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|date=April 2, 2018|accessdate=January 30, 2020}}</ref> Billy stated in a May 2018 interview that opening for Slayer on their farewell tour would be \"the final lap for [them] touring\" in support of ''Brotherhood of the Snake'', and added, \"We want our focus, during this and after this, to dive back into the songwriting process. We want to release a new album in 2019, so we need to get started soon.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/testaments-chuck-billy-we-want-to-release-a-new-album-in-2019/|title=TESTAMENT's CHUCK BILLY: 'We Want To Release A New Album In 2019'|website=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|date=May 9, 2018|accessdate=January 30, 2020}}</ref> A month later, Billy told [[Full Metal Jackie]] that, \"the goal is to get in the studio hopefully by January and have a record out hopefully by April.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/testament-frontman-hopes-to-begin-recording-new-album-in-january/|title=TESTAMENT Frontman Hopes To Begin Recording New Album In January|website=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|date=July 24, 2018|accessdate=January 30, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://loudwire.com/chuck-billy-testament-new-album-hopefully-april-2019/|title=Chuck Billy: Testament's New Album 'Hopefully' Out April of 2019|website=[[Loudwire|Loudwire.com]]|date=June 25, 2018|accessdate=January 30, 2020}}</ref> He also told ''Metal Heads Forever Magazine'' that, \"Me and Eric, we'll start really just creating and working, trying to get the next record out as soon as possible, because we have plans and hopes of setting a deadline on ourselves to have it out by summer 2019. We've got a lot of work ahead of us.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/testaments-chuck-billy-the-goal-is-to-have-next-album-out-by-summer-2019/|title=TESTAMENT's CHUCK BILLY: The Goal Is To Have Next Album Out 'By Summer 2019'|website=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|date=July 31, 2018|accessdate=January 30, 2020}}</ref> Billy told ''Talking Metal'' podcast in August 2018 that the band would start work on the new album after their tour with Slayer, and added, \"Our hopes and dreams would be to get in the studio by January and have an album out by the summer.\" He also said that they would work with [[Andy Sneap]] as the album's mixer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/testament-frontman-its-time-to-buckle-down-and-try-to-get-some-music-written/|title=TESTAMENT Frontman: 'It's Time To Buckle Down And Try To Get Some Music Written'|website=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|date=August 8, 2018|accessdate=January 30, 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn a January 2019 interview with Jimmy Kay of Canada's The Metal Voice, Billy confirmed that Testament had been writing songs for their thirteenth album, and added, \"We should have it out hopefully by July. Hopefully we'll get into the studio by April. That's the goal.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/testaments-chuck-billy-on-next-album-hopefully-well-get-into-the-studio-by-april/|title=TESTAMENT's CHUCK BILLY On Next Album: 'Hopefully We'll Get Into The Studio By April'|website=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|date=January 26, 2019|accessdate=January 30, 2020}}</ref> A month later, Billy announced on social media that work on the new album had started,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://metaladdicts.com/site/testament-are-working-on-new-album/|title=TESTAMENT Are Working On New Album|website=MetalAddicts.com|date=February 8, 2019|accessdate=January 30, 2020}}</ref> and pre-production began in May.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/testament-in-pre-production-for-new-album-its-gonna-be-a-monster-record/|title=TESTAMENT In Pre-Production For New Album: 'It's Gonna Be A Monster Record'|website=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|date=May 5, 2019|accessdate=January 30, 2020}}</ref> Drummer [[Gene Hoglan]] revealed in a June 2019 interview on the \"Talk Toomey\" podcast that the band had finished recording the album for a 2019 or early 2020 release.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/testament-has-finished-recording-new-album-says-gene-hoglan/|title=TESTAMENT Has Finished Recording New Album, Says GENE HOGLAN|website=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|date=June 18, 2019|accessdate=January 30, 2020}}</ref> Peterson announced later that month that it would be released in January 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/testaments-new-album-to-be-released-in-january-2020/|title=TESTAMENT's New Album To Be Released In January 2020|website=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|accessdate=June 23, 2019|date=June 23, 2019}}</ref> In an interview at a [[Metal Allegiance]] concert in Anaheim on January 16, 2020, Billy revealed that the then-still-untitled album would be released on April 3.<ref name=\"april2020\">{{cite web|url=https://www.blabbermouth.net/news/testaments-new-album-gets-official-release-date/|title=TESTAMENT's New Album Gets Official Release Date|website=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|accessdate=January 18, 2020|date=January 18, 2020}}</ref> It was later revealed that the album would be titled ''Titans of Creation''.<ref name=\"blabbermouth\" /><ref name=\"itunes\"/>\n\n==Reception==\n{{Album ratings\n<!-- Aggregate scores -->\n| MC         = \n<!-- Reviewers -->\n| rev1       = [[Blabbermouth.net]]<ref name=\"blabbermouth.net\">{{cite web |url=https://www.blabbermouth.net/cdreviews/titans-of-creation/|title=CD Reviews - Titans Of Creation Testament|last=Roche|first=Jason|publisher=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|accessdate=April 10, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev1Score  = 8/10\n| rev2       = [[KNAC]]<ref name=\"knac.com\">{{cite web |url=http://knac.com/article.asp?ArticleID=35913|title=KNAC.COM - Reviews - TESTAMENT 'Titans Of Creation'|last=Atkinson|first=Peter|publisher=[[KNAC|knac.com]]|date=April 3, 2020|accessdate=April 10, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev2Score  = 3.5/5\n| rev3       = [[Metal Storm (webzine)|Metal Storm]]\n| rev3Score  = 6.0/10<ref name=\"Metal Storm\">{{cite web |title= Testament - Titans Of Creation review |url=http://metalstorm.net/pub/review.php?review_id=15485 |publisher=Metal Storm |accessdate=12 April 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n''Titans of Creation'' has received positive reviews from critics. Jason Roche of [[Blabbermouth.net]] gave the album a rating of eight out of ten and said, \"While Testament has in the past shown to be capable of much more in terms of lyrics and songcraft, the fact that the band is using their power in 2020 to simply put out a killer thrash record full of songs about well-worn topics such as World War III, serial killers from a generation ago, and the [[Heaven's Gate (religious group)|Heaven's Gate]] suicide cult is comforting and very welcome.\"<ref name=\"blabbermouth.net\" /> [[KNAC|KNAC.com]] contributor Peter Atkinson, who rated ''Titans of Creation'' 3.5 out of five, called it \"sort of kick in the ass we could all use right now. And the album most definitely kicks ass.\"<ref name=\"knac.com\" />\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n| title1 = Children of the Next Level\n| lyrics1 = {{hlist|[[Chuck Billy (vocalist)|Chuck Billy]]|[[Del James]]}}\n| music1 = [[Eric Peterson]]\n| length1 = 6:13\n| title2 = WWIII\n| lyrics2 = {{hlist|Billy|James}}\n| music2 = Peterson\n| length2 = 4:48\n| title3 = Dream Deceiver\n| lyrics3 = {{hlist|Billy|James}}\n| music3 = Peterson\n| length3 = 4:58\n| title4 = Night of the Witch\n| lyrics4 = {{hlist|Billy|Peterson|James}}\n| music4 = Peterson\n| length4 = 6:32\n| title5 = City of Angels\n| lyrics5 = {{hlist|Billy|James}}\n| musi