ir Race NX916 \"Aloha\" Breese-Wilde.jpg|80px]]\n|style=\"font-size:150%;\"| 11 || style=\"font-size:150%;\"| 6\n|[[Martin Jensen (aviator)|Martin Jensen]] || Paul Schluter\n|align=left| Lemon yellow with pink lei\n|style=\"font-size:150%;\"| 2\n|align=left style=\"font-size:90%;\" |\n|<ref name=Conant/><ref name=MT-19270816/> <ref name=HT-19270817/>\n|-\n! [[Travel Air 5000]] !! ''Woolaroc'' !! NX869\n| [[File:Woolaroc airplane by Tyler Thomson 1.jpg|80px]]\n|style=\"font-size:150%;\"| 9 || style=\"font-size:150%;\"| 7\n|Arthur Goebel || William J. Davis\n|align=left| Yellow and blue\n|style=\"font-size:150%;\"| 1\n|align=left style=\"font-size:90%;\" | Finished with {{convert|1+1/2|USpt|l}} of gas. Name originated from the \"woods, lakes, and rocks\" on the lands of the corporate sponsor, Phillips Petroleum.\n|<ref name=SB-Derby1/><ref name=MT-19270816/> <ref name=HT-19270817>{{cite news |url=https://cdnc.ucr.edu/?a=d&d=HT19270817.2.7 |title=Woolaroc Wins Honolulu Air Race |date=August 17, 1927 |author=Palmer, John N. |agency=United Press |newspaper=Healdsburg Tribune |accessdate=29 February 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! [[Swallow Monoplane]] !! ''Dallas Spirit'' !! NX941\n|[[File:Dole Air Race NX941 \"Dallas Spirit\" Swallow Monoplane.jpg|80px]]\n|style=\"font-size:150%;\"| 5 || style=\"font-size:150%;\"| 8\n|[[William Portwood Erwin]] || Alvin Eichwaldt\n|align=left| Green\n|style=\"font-size:150%;\"| DNS\n|align=left style=\"font-size:90%;\" | Originally to be navigated by Erwin's wife, Constance. Forced to return with engine trouble. Lost at sea while searching for missing ''Miss Doran'' and ''Golden Eagle''.\n|<ref name=SB-Derby1>{{cite news |url=http://archives.starbulletin.com/2003/12/29/features/story2.html |title=The Dole Derby, Chapter 1: The Pineapple King's Great Pacific Air Race |author=Burlingame, Burl |date=December 29, 2003 |newspaper=Honolulu Star-Bulletin |accessdate=29 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=MT-19270816/>\n|-\n! colspan=12 style=\"font-size:120%;\