.2.10 |title=Six Entrants for Dole Prize in Bay Section |agency=United Press |date=August 8, 1927 |newspaper=Healdsburg Tribune |accessdate=1 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! [[International Sportsman|International F-17W biplane]] !! ''Miss Hollydale'' !! NX912\n|[[File:Dole Air Race NX912 \"Miss Hollydale\" International F-17W.jpg|80px]]\n|style=\"font-size:150%;\"| 12 || style=\"font-size:150%;\"| \u2014\n|Frank L. Clarke || Jeff Warren\n|align=left| \n|style=\"font-size:150%;\"| WD\n|align=left style=\"font-size:90%;\" | Announced withdrawal and left abruptly on Aug 13.\n|<ref name=SPNP-19270813>{{cite news |url=https://cdnc.ucr.edu/?a=d&d=SPNP19270813.2.2 |title=Flyer Hops off for Honolulu: Airman Pulls Fast One on Dole Entries |date=August 13, 1927 |newspaper=San Pedro News-Pilot |agency=United Press |accessdate=1 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://azmemory.azlibrary.gov/digital/collection/dddispatch/id/5665/ |title=Views of Dole Flight Entrants |date=August 17, 1927 |newspaper=Douglas Daily Dispatch |page=3 |accessdate=2 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! Tremaine Hummingbird !! ''Spirit of John Rodgers'' !!\n|[[File:Dole Air Race Tremaine Humming Bird.jpg|80px]]\n|style=\"font-size:150%;\"| 13 || style=\"font-size:150%;\"| \u2014\n|George D. Covell || Richard S. Waggener\n|align=left| \n|style=\"font-size:150%;\"| X\n|align=left style=\"font-size:90%;\" | Original navigator L.P. Pawlikowski withdrew Aug 8 with illness. Crashed at Point Loma enroute to start of race on August 10. No survivors.\n|<ref name=SB-Derby1/><ref>{{cite news |url=https://cdnc.ucr.edu/?a=d&d=SBS19270811.1.1 |title=Navy Airmen Fall as Trip North Begun |agency=United Press |date=August 11, 1927 |newspaper=San Bernardino Sun |accessdate=1 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! Bryant Monoplane !! ''Angel of Los Angeles'' !! NX705\n|[[File:Dole Air Race NX705 \"Angel of Los Angeles\" Bryant Monoplane.jpg|80px]]\n|style=\"font-size:150%;\"| 14 || style=\"font-size:150%;\"| \u2014\n| colspan=2 | Arthur V. Rogers\n|align=left| \n|style=\"font-size:150%;\"| X\n|align=left style=\"font-size:90%;\" | Crashed during test flight at Western Air Express Field (Montebello) on August 12. No survivors.\n|<ref name=Conant/><ref>{{ASN accident |id=60096 |type= |title=ASN Wikibase Occurrence # 60096 |wikibase=yes |accessdate=1 March 2020 }}</ref> <ref>{{cite web |url=https://homesteadmuseum.wordpress.com/2019/07/10/from-point-a-to-point-b-the-crash-of-the-monoplane-angel-of-los-angeles-1927/ |title=From Point A to Point B: the Crash of the Monoplane 'Angel of Los Angeles', 1927 |author=Spitzzeri, Paul R. |date=July 10, 2019 |website=The Homestead Museum |accessdate=1 March 2020}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==See also==\n\n* [[List of aviation awards]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n===Further reading===\n{{div col}}\n* {{cite magazine |url=https://archive.org/details/aerodigest1119unse/page/250/mode/2up/ |title=The Dole Pacific Race |date=September 1927 |magazine=Aero Digest |pages=250\u2013255;366 |publisher=The Aeronautical Digest Publishing Corp. |volume=11 |number=3}}\n* {{cite news | first = Jane Eshleman | last = Conant | title = Death Dogged the Dolebirds: Pioneer Pacific Fliers Wrote Tragic Chapter in Air History | url = http://www.sfmuseum.org/hist10/27dolerace.html | work = San Francisco Call-Bulletin | date = October 10, 1955 | accessdate = September 12, 2010  }}\n* {{cite book |title=Great Adventure Stories |editor=Brent, Rafer |publisher=Bartholomew House |location=New York |url=https://archive.org/details/greatadventurest012839mbp |chapter=$35,000 Race to Death |author=Conant, Jane |pages=[https://archive.org/details/greatadventurest012839mbp/page/n178 175]\u2013200 |date=1958}}\n* {{cite journal |jstor=30235716 |title='The Dallas Spirit': The Last Fool Flight |author=Dealey, Ted |date=July 1959 |volume=63 |number=1 |pages=15\u201330 |journal=The Southwestern Historical Quarterly}}\n* {{cite book |last=Forden |first=Lesley |title=Glory Gamblers: The Story of the Dole Race |date=1